WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.473
Your best ideas don't wait for you to sit down.

00:00:02.914 --> 00:00:04.273
They arrive on a walk.

00:00:04.598 --> 00:00:05.596
Between meetings.

00:00:06.293 --> 00:00:08.325
While you're holding something else in your head.

00:00:08.928 --> 00:00:10.809
The question isn't where they come from —

00:00:11.250 --> 00:00:13.480
it's whether you can catch them before they slip.

00:00:14.176 --> 00:00:15.778
That's what Talkie is for.

00:00:16.475 --> 00:00:17.636
Three principles.

00:00:18.588 --> 00:00:19.435
Velocity.

00:00:20.248 --> 00:00:23.487
Your voice is the fastest path from thought to action.

00:00:24.184 --> 00:00:27.330
Speak it, and it lands — in your draft,

00:00:27.411 --> 00:00:31.533
your task list, your terminal, wherever you were already going.

00:00:32.229 --> 00:00:33.193
Sovereignty.

00:00:33.576 --> 00:00:35.654
Your words stay on your devices.

00:00:36.351 --> 00:00:38.569
We don't ship them to a cloud to be useful.

00:00:38.777 --> 00:00:41.668
The signal path is short, and it's yours.

00:00:42.620 --> 00:00:43.271
Flow.

00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:45.709
The cursor returns to where it started.

00:00:46.405 --> 00:00:48.356
Your hands stay where they were.

00:00:49.168 --> 00:00:51.339
Talkie doesn't ask you to leave what you're doing.

00:00:51.490 --> 00:00:53.313
Your voice is the fastest path.

00:00:53.917 --> 00:00:55.774
Don't let the tools slow you down.

